description:
CRITICAL (found by reviewer-correctness): If ValidateIdentity or EvaluatePolicy fails, the workflow returns via finalize() without sending on DecisionCh. goproxy blocks forever on `<-decisionCh`. The goproxy goroutine leaks and the deferred registry.Delete never runs.

Fix: Replace bare `decision := <-decisionCh` with:
```go
select {
case decision := <-decisionCh:
    // FetchAndInject succeeded
case <-workflowDone(run):
    // Workflow completed without sending decision — check result for denial
case <-time.After(45 * time.Second):
    // Timeout safety net
}
```

Also add a NotifyDenial local activity at every early-return path, OR use a deferred cleanup pattern in the workflow.

Files: credential-proxy/proxy/handlers.go (goproxy side), credential-proxy/workflows/proxy_workflow.go (workflow side)
